How to setup diff diff properties value in diff environment?

By profiles..
we will use profiles.

we can creatre application_qa.yml, application_prod.properties

we can set spring.profiles.active=prod,qa like this .

At first we need to understand which all configuration and properties changes when we chnage the environment
then we can decide which config should be inside default properties file or which one should be inside specific one


we need to tell spring boot , when qa asks in default then this yml should call
spring:
  config:
    activate:
      on-profile:"qa"

spring:
  config:
    activate:
      on-profile:"prod"

then we have to tell in default properties to import the application_qa.yml and application_prod.yml
we can mention in default as follows

spring:
  config:
    import:
      - "application_qa.yml"
      - "application_prod.yml"
  profiles:
    active:
      - "qa"
then we need to mention which profile to start in default properties file.


we need to mannualy change in default config files when we change the environment, so it will not recommeded to change and it will not fesiable solution to do so.
Then we need to externalize the configurations using command line runner.

Spring boot automatically converts key and value pairs and it has highest preference

we need to follow --build.version=1.1

JVM system properties has less prefernce but highest preference trhen Environment
                -Dbuild.version=2.2
Environment variables are unversal support
    - all lettter as uppere case
    - all dots(.) should be under_score(_)
    BUILD_VERSION=1.1


